[RECIPE] Rice is a daily staple in my household. And like other busy moms, I'm always looking out for convenient one-pot meal ideas.
•
Did you know that there are several interesting #ricerecipes on @songhe.rice website? One of them - Japanese Yam Rice - caught my attention.
•
This recipe uses just 4 main ingredients: rice, chicken, Japanese yam, and spinach. The result is a delicious yet wholesome all-in-one meal!
•
I made some modifications to the original recipe. Below is my version. Check out my #cookingvideo as well!
•
#AromacookeryRecipeSongheRiceJapaneseYamRice
•
INGREDIENTS
1.5 cups SongHe Fragrant Rice, washed and drained (1 cup=250ml)
2 tbsp Rice Field 100% Rice Bran Oil
5 slices ginger
300gm boneless chicken thigh
150gm Japanese yam (淮山 huai shan/ 山药 shan yao)
100gm Chinese spinach
1 tsp salt
1.5 cups water
•
MARINADE for chicken:
1 tsp light soy sauce
1 tsp oyster sauce
1 tsp sugar
1 tsp sesame oil
1 tsp corn starch
•
METHOD
1. Remove skin from boneless chicken leg. Cut into cubes. Mix well with marinade ingredients. Cover and leave for at least 30 minutes.
•
2. Wash and rinse the rice well. Leave in a colander to let water drain through.
•
3. Peel and cut Japanese yam into bite-sized chunks. Set aside.
•
4. In a wok or non-stick pan, heat oil and stir-fry ginger until fragrant. Add chicken, and stir-fry until half done. Do not overcook the chicken while in the wok.
•
5. Add drained rice and stir-fry for 3-5 minutes until rice grains are dry and separate.
•
6. Transfer rice and chicken into rice cooker. Add salt and water. Place Japanese yam on top.
•
7. Around 12 minutes before the rice is done, place chopped spinach on top of rice to steam-cook.
•
8. When the rice is cooked, use a spatula to mix all ingredients. Stir gently to avoid smashing the Japanese yam. Optional: Add some pre-soaked goji berries if you like.
•
9. Cover the lid for another 5 minutes. Dish up, serve hot and enjoy! 🍚😋
•
*Note 1: Rice to water ratio is 1:1
*Note 2: You can substitute water with chicken stock. Reduce amount of salt in recipe if necessary.
•
Original recipe from https://tspsonghe.com.sg/en/recipes/
